# LNP64 MC encoding contract v0.
# Pipe-delimited fields: group|format|opcodes|operands|relocations|llvm_surface
# fixed32_no_operand: opcode[31:24], reserved[23:0]=0; implemented first for NOP and RET
# fixed32_ri: opcode[31:24], rd[23:19], reserved[18:16], imm16[15:0]
# fixed32_reg_u32_tail: opcode[31:24], rd[23:19], reserved[18:0], followed by little-endian imm32/address payload
# fixed32_rr: opcode[31:24], rd[23:19], rs[18:14], reserved[13:0]
# fixed32_rrr: opcode[31:24], rd[23:19], rs1[18:14], rs2[13:9], reserved[8:0]
# fixed32_rri_simm14: opcode[31:24], rd[23:19], rs[18:14], simm14[13:0]
# fixed32_mem_base_simm: opcode[31:24], reg[23:19], base[18:14], simm14[13:0]
# fixed32_branch26: opcode[31:24], simm24_words[23:0]; encodes aligned signed 26-bit byte displacement
# fixed32_reg_or_none: opcode[31:24], reg[23:19], reserved[18:0] or all reserved for RET
# fixed32_native4: opcode[31:24], rd[23:19], cap[18:14], arg0[13:9], arg1[8:4], reserved[3:0]
# fixed32_clone_control: clone/thread control opcodes using fixed32_rrr.
# fixed32_mmap_bootstrap_control: compact LLVM bootstrap VMA control form.
# Final __lnp_mmap remains blocked on the F9 argument-block encoding described
# in hardware_design.md section 17.
# fixed32_cset: opcode[31:24], rd[23:19], reserved[18:0]; materializes current FLAGS as 0/1
# fixed32_compat_metadata: transitional status-in-r1 compatibility metadata/time/fcntl helpers.
# fixed32_compat_namespace: transitional status-in-r1 namespace/path compatibility helpers; five-register forms use a little-endian u32 tail carrying the fifth GPR id.
